stylometry: Decision trees are important in problem solving becaue they take extensive complex information and exactly show the sequences of it.  Decision trees help paint a picture of the managerial decision process.  It shows the monetary values as well as probabilities.  It is good to mapout complex problems.  They are used to find out what outcomes come from certain decisions that could be made.  It gives information on information.  A decision tree can be used to solve a companies problem of trying to make a decision if they should run a new advertising campaign.  It would show the probabilities of the new advertising campaign being sucesfull and vis-versa.  It would map out the sequence of decisions that could be made.
